&gt;As an aside, we count asserts instead of tests because it&#39;s a finer grained
&gt;metric.  Right now we only have 8 functional test methods, but 170
&gt;assertions.  When we add to a functional test we don&#39;t create a new test
&gt;method, we add some more assertions to an already existing test.  It would
&gt;be harder to see progress if we tracked test cases.

My version of JUnit doesn&#39;t count asserts, but it probably should, so it
would provide a warning if a testcase has no assertions in it.


